# Component Design System

## Folder structure

- `src/components/ui/`: shadcn primitives only. Do not add feature logic here.
- `src/components/{domain}/`: reusable feature UI (`cv/`, `agent/`, `layout/`).
- `src/app/**/page.tsx`: thin composition only. No large inline JSX or business logic.

## When to extract a component

Extract when:
- Used on 2+ pages, or
- It is a design-system unit (preview card, section list, assistant bubble).

## Conventions

- One primary export per file, `PascalCase` filename matching export.
- Props over one-off styling. Shared types live in `src/lib/types/`.
- Agent/assistant UI belongs in `src/components/agent/` (status badge, progress stream, floating panel).
- CV domain UI belongs in `src/components/cv/` (preview, grids, lists, workspace).
- Data access goes through `src/lib/api/cv-api.ts`, not direct store imports from pages.
- Use plain, non-technical copy in all user-facing text. **No em dashes** (see `no-em-dash.mdc`).
- Colocate private helpers in the same file only when not reusable elsewhere.

## Shell layout: one purpose per zone

- **`PageHeader`**: platform navigation only (logo, nav, account menu). Do not put create/import/export or other document actions here.
- **`PageTitle`**: page heading plus optional **page actions** (e.g. Import a resume) aligned top-right of the title row.
- **`AppWorkspace` toolbar**: in-editor actions for the open document (download, duplicate, etc.), not catalog-level create/import.

```tsx
// BAD: import lives in the global header
<CatalogShell actions={<Button>Import a resume</Button>} /> // if passed to PageHeader

// GOOD: import beside the page title
<CatalogShell title="Resumes" actions={<Button>Import a resume</Button>} />
// CatalogShell forwards actions to PageTitle, not PageHeader
```

## Examples

```tsx
// BAD: page fetches data inline instead of API layer
import { listResumes } from "./local-data";

// GOOD: page uses API layer
import { listResumes } from "@/lib/api/cv-api";
```

```tsx
// BAD: feature component in ui/
src/components/ui/cv-preview.tsx

// GOOD: domain folder
src/components/cv/cv-preview.tsx
```
